<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,760,713,928]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,713,736]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was described based on four females from Mentawai Islands (
<figureCitation box="[498,577,745,768]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="18.[151,188,1932,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,193,1862]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[151,1437,187,1862]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 74–83. Habitus of Taumacera. 74– T. fulvovirens (Laboissière 1929) (female, syntype); 75 – T. fulvovirens (male); 76 – T. laevipennis (Jacoby, 1886) (male); 77 – T. maculata (Baly, 1886) (male, syntype); 78 – T.midtibialis Mohamedsaid, 1998 (male); 79 – T.seminigra Reid, 1999 (male, syntype of Metellus nigripennis Jacoby, 1899); 80 – T. subapicalis Mohamedsaid, 1993 (male); 81 – T. sucki Weise, 1922 (male, holotype of T. martapurensis Mohamedsaid, 1998); 82 – T. tibialis Mohamedsaid, 1994 (male); 83 – T. uniformis (Jacoby, 1891) (male, syntype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505536/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="REID C. A. M." box="[595,720,745,768]" firstAuthor="REID" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Entomology" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 9" part="38" refId="ref33192" refString="REID C. A. M. 1999: Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae). Australian Journal of Entomology 38: 1 - 9." title="Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae)" type="journal article" year="1999">REID (1999)</bibRefCitation>
did not classify 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laboissiere" authorityYear="1929" box="[283,429,777,800]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvovirens">
<emphasis box="[283,429,777,800]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">T. fulvovirens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[506,604,777,800]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deusta">
<emphasis box="[506,604,777,800]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">T. deusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group because males were unknown to him. I found altogether four males with characteristically modified antennae (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="18.[151,188,1932,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,193,1862]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[151,1437,187,1862]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 74–83. Habitus of Taumacera. 74– T. fulvovirens (Laboissière 1929) (female, syntype); 75 – T. fulvovirens (male); 76 – T. laevipennis (Jacoby, 1886) (male); 77 – T. maculata (Baly, 1886) (male, syntype); 78 – T.midtibialis Mohamedsaid, 1998 (male); 79 – T.seminigra Reid, 1999 (male, syntype of Metellus nigripennis Jacoby, 1899); 80 – T. subapicalis Mohamedsaid, 1993 (male); 81 – T. sucki Weise, 1922 (male, holotype of T. martapurensis Mohamedsaid, 1998); 82 – T. tibialis Mohamedsaid, 1994 (male); 83 – T. uniformis (Jacoby, 1891) (male, syntype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505536/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
) and accordingly I assign 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laboissiere" authorityYear="1929" box="[453,596,873,896]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvovirens">
<emphasis box="[453,596,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">T. fulvovirens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[665,760,873,896]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deusta">
<emphasis box="[665,760,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">T. deusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group.
</paragraph>
